The paper deals with communication complexity, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) as it uses mutual information as a measure of distributional complexity. The Vapnik-Chervonenkis dimension and pseudo-dimension are also mentioned, which are concepts from computational learning theory and fall under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves probability theory and statistics, which are relevant to the field of data mining (cs.DM). Finally, the paper involves lower bounds and complexity measures, which are relevant to the field of machine learning (cs.LG).
